The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bangla umpire

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Sheikh Kamrul Hossain, an umpire of Bangladesh Cricket Board, is officiating matches in the Ambar Roy sub-junior cricket tournament. Hossain, who is the first secretary of the Bangladesh High Commission in the city, had earlier expressed his desire to conduct matches here. 

We dont have any league or senior tournament matches now and so we have allotted him the sub-junior matches, CAB joint secretary Bablu Kolay said. 




